<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A police officer was stabbed in the leg while responding to a call-out in Eastbourne as a man, 42, is arrested on suspicion of attempted murder.</p>

<p>The attack happened after police dealt with an unrelated matter on Terminus Road in the East Sussex town at around 1am this morning.  </p>

<p>The officer, who suffered a serious stab injury to his leg, managed to self-administer medical treatment while two officers captured the suspect.</p>

<p>A handout CCTV image issued by Sussex Police showing a group of people seen on Terminus Road shortly before the attack took place, some of whom may have spoken to the suspect</p>

<p>The actions of officers to detain the suspect following the attack were praised by Sussex Police's chief constable. </p>

<p>The injured officer was taken to the Royal Sussex County Hospital in Brighton for further treatment.</p>

<p>A 42-year-old man from Eastbourne was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder, wounding with intent and assault by beating of an emergency worker.</p>

<p>He remains in custody for questioning.</p>

<p>Praising her officers, Chief Constable Jo Shiner said: 'The events overnight starkly demonstrate the risk that all police officers and frontline staff face every day whilst performing their duties to protect the public.</p>

<p>'It is thanks to comprehensive training and the fast thinking of those at the scene that I am not reporting something far more serious today.</p>

<p>CCTV handout image of a group of people who are detectives are keen to speak to in relation to the attack. A 42-year-old man was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder</p>

<p>'The injured officer was able to move away and self-administer medical intervention whilst his two junior colleagues - both just 15 months into their policing careers - apprehended the suspect.</p>

<p>'The actions of all three officers, as well as colleagues who swiftly came to their aid, are to be commended.'</p>

<p>The force has released CCTV images in an appeal to trace witnesses to the attack, some of whom may have talked to the suspect.</p>
